1. Permission to Use
COOL Framework (hereafter “COOL”), including its text, structure, design principles,
and Core Profile format, may be used, modified, and redistributed freely.
Commercial use is also permitted without restriction.

2. Name Protection
2-1. The name “COOL” must not be removed, altered, or replaced.
Any derivative work must clearly state that it is based on or derived from COOL.

2-2. Names that cause confusion with COOL are prohibited, including:
- Slightly altered names (e.g., COOLer, COOLX, COOL++, etc.)
- Names intended to mimic or be mistaken for COOL
- Any attempt to rebrand COOL as an original work of another party

3. Attribution Requirement
All uses of COOL must include the following credit:

Created by Coolar — Original Creator of the COOL Framework

A translation or equivalent statement is also acceptable.

4. Derivative Works
If you publish or distribute a derivative work:
- You must state that it is based on or derived from COOL.
- You must not remove or modify the COOL name or the original creator attribution.
- You must not claim the structural features of COOL as entirely your own invention.

5. Prohibited Actions
The following actions are strictly forbidden:
- Claiming COOL as an original work not created by Coolar
- Attempting to appropriate the COOL brand, name, or conceptual framework
- Fraudulent or malicious use of COOL

6. Disclaimer
Coolar assumes no responsibility for any damages resulting from the use of COOL.

7. License Updates
This license may be updated by Coolar. Previously published versions remain valid
and may continue to be used.

